LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 417
BY APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO THE APPROPRIATION TO THE STATE BOARD OF EDUCATION FOR COMMUNITY
3 COLLEGES; APPROPRIATING ADDITIONAL MONEYS TO THE STATE BOARD OF EDU-
4 CATION FOR COMMUNITY COLLEGES FOR FISCAL YEAR 2026; PROVIDING FOR THE
5 TRANSITION TO OUTCOMES-BASED FUNDING FOR COMMUNITY COLLEGES; PROVIDING
6 FOR CONDITIONS, LIMITATIONS, AND RESTRICTIONS; AND DECLARING AN EMER-
7 GENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
8 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
9 SECTION 1. In addition to any other appropriation provided by law,
10 there is hereby appropriated to the State Board of Education for Community
11 Colleges the following amounts to be expended according to the designated
12 programs for personnel costs from the General Fund for the period July 1,
13 2025, through June 30, 2026:
14 FOR:
15 COLLEGE OF EASTERN IDAHO: $496,800
16 COLLEGE OF SOUTHERN IDAHO: $690,000
17 COLLEGE OF WESTERN IDAHO: $493,000
18 TOTAL $1,679,800
19 SECTION 2. TRANSITIONING TO OUTCOMES-BASED FUNDING IN HIGHER EDU-
20 CATION. The Office of the State Board of Education shall develop an out-
21 comes-based funding model to replace the Enrollment Workload Adjustment for
22 Idaho's community colleges. The Office of the State Board shall deliver a
23 written proposal to the Joint Finance-Appropriations Committee by December
24 31, 2025, with a plan for implementation of the new funding model in fis-
25 cal year 2028 or earlier. The Office of the State Board of Education shall
26 provide written reports to the Joint Finance-Appropriations Committee on
27 a quarterly basis detailing progress towards the outcomes-based funding
28 model. The format and content of this report will be determined in con-
29 sultation with the Budget and Policy Analysis Division of the Legislative
30 Services Office.
31 SECTION 3. CONDITIONS, LIMITATIONS, AND RESTRICTIONS. Appropriations
32 made pursuant to this act are subject to the conditions, limitations, and re-
33 strictions specified in this act.
34 SECTION 4. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
35 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
36 July 1, 2025.

